'''约翰·泰勒'''（{{lang-en|John Tyler}}，{{bd|1790年|3月29日|1862年|1月18日}}<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/L424-JDY/president-john-tyler-iv-1790-1862 | title = President John Tyler IV | website = FamilySearch | access-date = 2021-11-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191003040328/https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/L424-JDY/president-john-tyler-iv-1790-1862 | dead-url = no | archive-date = 2019-10-03 }}</ref>）是第十任美国总统和副总统，他1840年与[[輝格黨_(美國)|辉格党]]总统候选人[[威廉·亨利·哈里森|威廉·亨利·哈里森]]搭档[[1840年威廉·亨利·哈里森竞选美国总统|赢得大选]]，1841年就任副总统；哈里森入主白宫仅一个月就在同年四月病逝，泰勒继任直到1845年任期结束。泰勒坚决支持并提倡[[州权|州权]]，对[[美國奴隸制度|奴隶制问题]]也不例外，担任总统期间，他只愿在不侵犯州权的前提下推动国家权力政策。泰勒意外登上总统宝座对[[亨利·克莱|亨利·克莱]]等政治家的总统抱负构成威胁，他同两大政党逐渐形同陌路。

[[泰勒家族|泰勒家族]]是弗吉尼亚名门，与同期美国南部大部分望族一样是奴隶主，泰勒在政坛动荡之际成为全国名流。[[民主共和黨|民主共和黨]]是19世纪20年代美国[[善意时代|仅有的政党]]，但没几年就随派系分裂。他本是[[美国民主党历史|民主党人]]，但在[[拒行联邦法规危机|拒行联邦法规危机]]时反对[[安德鲁·杰克逊|安德鲁·杰克逊]]，认为杰克逊的行为侵犯州权，谴责总统在[[银行战争|银行战争]]期间扩大行政权力。泰勒投向[[輝格黨_(美國)|辉格党]]怀抱，先后担任弗吉尼亚州议员、州长、联邦众议员、联邦参议员。为吸引主张州权的南方选民，辉格党安排泰勒与哈里森搭档，战胜竞选连任的[[马丁·范布伦|马丁·范布伦]]。

哈里森总统上任仅一个月就病逝，泰勒是首位未经选举上台的美国总统；美国史上其他未经选举上台的总统任职时间都不及泰勒。《美国宪法》语焉不详，泰勒抢先行动马上[[美国总统宣誓就职|宣誓就职]]并搬进[[白宮|白宮]]，接掌全部总统权力，成为后世副总统继位先例并写入[[美利坚合众国宪法第二十五条修正案|美利坚合众国宪法第二十五条修正案]]。泰勒签署辉格党主导国会通过的部分法案，但他力主[[狭义解释宪法派|从严解读宪法]]，否决该党创办国民银行、提升关税的法案。泰勒认为政策应由总统而非国会主导，企图绕过肯塔基州联邦参议员克莱为首的辉格党势力。泰勒上台后不久大部分内阁辞职，辉格党人嘲笑他是“碰巧总统”，甚至把他开除出党。泰勒是首位遭国会推翻否决的总统，他在国内政策陷入僵局，但外交领域不无小补，与英国签署《[[韦伯斯特－阿什伯顿条约|韦伯斯特－阿什伯顿条约]]》并同[[清朝|清朝]]签订《[[望廈條約|望廈條約]]》。

[[德克萨斯共和国|德克萨斯共和国]]1836年脱离墨西哥，坚信[[昭昭天命|昭昭天命]]的泰勒竭力推动该国并入联邦，认为美国经济将由此迎来重大机遇。他一度考虑竞选连任，但辉格党和民主党都无意支持，最后泰勒放弃竞选支持同样主张兼并德克萨斯的[[詹姆斯·诺克斯·波尔克|詹姆斯·诺克斯·波尔克]]。波尔克胜出后泰勒在离任三天前签署兼并德克萨斯的法案，波尔克上台后落实程序。1861年[[南北战争|南北战争]]爆发，泰勒支持[[美利堅聯盟國|邦联]]并在去世前不久赢得[[美利坚联盟国国会|众议员]]席位。学者称赞泰勒政治立场坚定，但史学家评比[[美国总统历史排名|美国总统历史排名]]时普遍将他排在偏后。与其他总统相比，泰勒在美国文化记忆里形象模糊，记得他的人很少。<ref name="Monroe-2003">{{cite book | last = Monroe | first = Dan | title = The Republican Vision of John Tyler | url = https://archive.org/details/republicanvision00monr | publisher = Texas A&M University Press | year = 2003 | isbn = 978-1-58544-216-4 | page = [https://archive.org/details/republicanvision00monr/page/n13 3] | quote = The vicious political infighting that characterized his term probably accounts for the low regard with which the Tyler presidency has been held by historians. His presidency is generally ranked as one of the least successful, despite achievements like the Webster–Ashburton treaty which heralded the prospect of improved relations with Great Britain, and the annexation of Texas, which added millions of acres to the national domain.}}</ref><ref name="millerlegacy">{{cite web | url = https://millercenter.org/president/tyler/impact-and-legacy | title = John Tyler: Impact and Legacy | author = William Freehling | publisher = The University of Virginia | work = Miller Center | access-date = 2021-11-27 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211126121928/https://millercenter.org/president/tyler/impact-and-legacy | archive-date = 2021-11-26 | dead-url = no | quote = By claiming the right to a fully functioning and empowered presidency instead of relinquishing the office or accepting limits on his powers, Tyler set a hugely important precedent. ... Unfortunately, Tyler proved much better at taking over the presidency than at actually being President. }}</ref><ref name="Foreign affairs" /><ref name="legacy">{{cite book | last = Crapol | first = Edward P. | title = John Tyler, the Accidental President | publisher = University of North Carolina Press | year = 2006 | isbn = 978-0-8078-3041-3 | access-date = 2021-11-23 | url = https://archive.org/details/johntyleracciden00edwa | quote = John Tyler is not one of the famous or better-known American presidents. ... Other biographers and historians have argued that John Tyler was a hapless and inept chief executive whose presidency was seriously flawed. Although acknowledging that Tyler was not a great president, I believe he was a stronger and more effective President than generally remembered. | pages = 2–3}}</ref><ref name="Seager-quote">{{cite book | last = Seager | first = Robert, II | title = And Tyler Too: A Biography of John and Julia Gardiner Tyler | location = New York | publisher = McGraw-Hill | year = 1963 | oclc = 424866 | access-date = 2021-11-23 | url = https://archive.org/details/andtylertooabiog013722mbp | page = xiii, xvi | quote = Yet John Tyler has become one of America's most obscure Chief Executives. His countrymen generally remember him, if they have heard of him at all, as the rhyming end of a catchy campaign slogan.... Yet I find him to be a courageous, principled man, a fair and honest fighter for his beliefs. He was a President without a party....True, he was neither a great President nor a great intellectual. ... Save for the success of his Texas policy and his Maine Boundary treaty with Great Britain, his administration has been and must be counted an unsuccessful one by any modern measure of accomplishment.}}</ref>

== 早年经历和教育 ==
约翰·泰勒1790年3月29日生于弗吉尼亚州蓄奴家族，是[[弗吉尼亚早期家族|弗吉尼亚早期家族]]后裔，与未来[[竞选搭档|竞选搭档]][[威廉·亨利·哈里森|威廉·亨利·哈里森]]一样来自[[查爾斯城縣_(維吉尼亞州)|查尔斯城县]]<ref>{{cite book | title = Affairs of State: The Untold History of Presidential Love, Sex, and Scandal, 1789–1900 | first = Robert P. | last = Watson | publisher = Lynn University | year = 2012 | page = 203 | isbn = 978-1442218352}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title = The World Almanac & Book of Facts | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=iHI3AAAAMAAJ&redir_esc=y | year = 1949 | publisher = Newspaper Enterprise Association | page = 110 | access-date = 2021-11-24 | archive-date = 2022-01-19 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220119095737/https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=iHI3AAAAMAAJ&redir_esc=y | dead-url = no }}</ref>。[[泰勒家族|泰勒家族]]祖上是英格兰移民，可追溯至17世纪殖民地时代的[[威廉斯堡_(弗吉尼亚州)|威廉斯堡]]。父亲[[老约翰·泰勒|老约翰·泰勒]]又称法官泰勒，是[[托马斯·杰斐逊|托马斯·杰斐逊]]的好友兼大学室友，曾与威廉之父[[本杰明·哈里森五世|本杰明·哈里森五世]]一起在[[弗吉尼亚州众议院|弗吉尼亚州众议院]]任职。老泰勒担任州众议院议长四年，还曾出任[[美国各州法院系统|州法院]]法官、[[維珍尼亞州州長|維珍尼亞州州長]]、驻[[里士满_(弗吉尼亚州)|里士满]][[美国弗吉尼亚东区联邦地区法院|美国弗吉尼亚东区联邦地区法院]]法官。夫人玛丽·马罗·阿米斯特德的父亲是[[新肯特縣_(維吉尼亞州)|新肯特县]]显赫种植园主罗伯特·布斯·阿米斯特德，曾任一届弗吉尼亚殖民地议员。玛丽1797年因[[中風|中風]]撒手人寰，此时儿子约翰只有七岁。<ref name="Chitwood-1964">{{cite book | last = Chitwood | first = Oliver Perry | title = John Tyler, Champion of the Old South | publisher = Russell & Russell | year = 1964 | orig-year = Orig. 1939, Appleton-Century | oclc = 424864}}</ref>{{rp|4–7, 12}}<ref name="Crapol-2006">{{cite book | last = Crapol | first = Edward P. | title = John Tyler, the Accidental President | publisher = University of North Carolina Press | year = 2006 | url = https://archive.org/details/johntyleracciden00edwa | isbn = 978-0-8078-3041-3 | access-date = 2021-11-23}}</ref>{{rp|30–31}}

泰勒有两兄弟五姐妹，在占地五平方公里的[[格林韦种植园|格林韦种植园]]长大，庄园由父亲建成，共有六间卧室。[[弗吉尼亚州奴隶制历史|奴隶]]种植小麦、玉米、烟草等各种作物，<ref name="Chitwood-1964" />{{rp|10–11}}<ref name="Crapol-2006" />{{rp|30}}父亲为孩子的导师支付高额报酬<ref name="Leahy-2006">{{cite journal | last = Leahy | first = Christopher | title = Torn Between Family and Politics: John Tyler's Struggle for Balance | journal = The Virginia Magazine of History and Biography | volume = 114 | number = 3 | year = 2006 | pages = 323–355}}</ref>{{rp|325–326}}。泰勒身体虚弱，长大后也一直很瘦而且容易腹泻<ref name="Seager-1963">{{cite book | last = Seager | first = Robert, II | title = And Tyler Too: A Biography of John and Julia Gardiner Tyler | location = New York | url = https://archive.org/details/andtylertooabiog013722mbp | publisher = McGraw-Hill | year = 1963 | oclc = 424866 | access-date = 2021-11-23}}</ref>{{rp|48}}。12岁时他遵循家族传统到[[威廉與瑪麗學院|威廉與瑪麗學院]]读预科，1807年在该校大学毕业时只有17岁。泰勒的经济观受[[亚当·斯密|亚当·斯密]]《[[國富論|國富論]]》影响，一生钟爱[[威廉·莎士比亚|威廉·莎士比亚]]。校长[[詹姆斯·麦迪逊_(主教)|詹姆斯·麦迪逊]]对泰勒亦师亦父，影响很大。<ref name="Chitwood-1964" />{{rp|14–18}}<ref name="Crapol-2006" />{{rp|31–34}}<ref name="Seager-1963" />{{rp|50}}

泰勒毕业后向担任州法官的父亲学法律，后拜入前[[美國司法部長|美国总检察长]][[埃德蒙·伦道夫|埃德蒙·伦道夫]]门下<ref name="Chitwood-1964" />{{rp|20–21}}<ref name="Crapol-2006" />{{rp|35–36}}。

== 种植园主和律师 ==
考核法官忘记询问年龄，结果尚未达到年龄下限的泰勒19岁便取得律师从业资格。父亲此时担任弗吉尼亚州长（1808至1811年），小泰勒在州首府里士满开始执业。<ref name="Chitwood-1964" />{{rp|20–21}}<ref name="Crapol-2006" />{{rp|35–36}}。1810年联邦政府人口普查显示“约翰·泰勒”（估计指州长）在里士满有八名奴隶<ref>1810 U.S. Federal Census for Richmond (independent city), Virginia p. 70 of 71, though header missing, and p. 63 appears "Jno. Taylor"</ref>，[[亨利科縣|亨利科縣]]可能有五名<ref>1810 U.S. Federal Census for Henrico County, Virginia, name on p. 23 of 44 appears nonresident on ancestry.com</ref>，查尔斯城县可能有26名<ref>1810 U.S. Federal Census for Charles City County, Virginia, name does not appear on damaged p. 1 of 24 linked on ancestry.com</ref>。

1813年老泰勒去世，小泰勒买下伍德伯恩种植园住到1821年<ref>{{cite web | author = Virginia Historic Landmarks Commission Staff | date = 1977-04 | page = 3 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180618150236/http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/Counties/CharlesCity/018-0052_Woodburn_1978_Final_Nomination.pdf | access-date = 2018-06-18 | archive-date = 2018-06-18 | dead-url = yes | url = http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/Counties/CharlesCity/018-0052_Woodburn_1978_Final_Nomination.pdf | title = National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Woodburn | format = PDF }}</ref>。他从父亲的遗产中继承13名奴隶，1820年在种植园拥有24名奴隶，但1820年人口普查数据显示只有八名奴隶在种植园务农<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.whitehousehistory.org/the-enslaved-households-of-president-john-tyler | title = The Enslaved Households of President John Tyler | publisher = White House Historical Association | access-date = 2021-11-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210723183804/https://www.whitehousehistory.org/the-enslaved-households-of-president-john-tyler | archive-date = 2021-07-23 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>1820 U.S. Federal Census for Charles City County p. 5 of 13 at ancestry.com</ref>。

